# S167: large tile-archive backup and poi-icon style-variant archive.
# The README.md inside the archive dir stays tracked so the archive is
# self-documenting; the 471 MB of PNG files are local-only.
tools/tile-bake/dist/salem_tiles_preS167.sqlite.bak
docs/archive/poi-icons-unused-styles_archived_*/**/*.png
docs/archive/poi-icons-unused-styles_archived_*/**/*.webp
docs/archive/poi-icons-unused-styles_archived_*/**/*.jpg

# IDE / tool caches
.kotlin/
.claude/
**/__pycache__/

# S245: operator legal records (Certificate of Organization etc.) — local-only,
# not shipped in the public repo. The entity facts that callers need are in
# docs/PRIVACY-POLICY-V1.md + the operating-entity memory.
LegalDocuments/

# S256: salem_tiles.sqlite (262 MB) is NOT tracked in git — exceeds
# GitHub's 100 MB blob limit and is a generated build artifact anyway. It
# lives at app-salem-tiles-pack/src/main/assets/salem_tiles.sqlite locally
# (consumed by the install-time Asset Pack module) and at tools/tile-bake/
# dist/salem_tiles.sqlite (pipeline staging). Both are regenerable; see
# tools/tile-bake/merge-into-bundle.js (canonical bake), then copy the
# output into app-salem-tiles-pack/src/main/assets/ before
# :app-salem:bundleRelease. ASSETS-MANIFEST.md documents the procedure.
tools/tile-bake/dist/salem_tiles.sqlite
app-salem-tiles-pack/src/main/assets/salem_tiles.sqlite

# DrK/ — Dr. K's authoritative POI content drafts (.docx / .odt). These ARE
# tracked: they are the source of truth that hand-promotes into salem_pois via
# the publish chain. Only block USB-mount detritus that lands here when a
# Windows / FAT32 stick gets plugged in (FOUND.000 = chkdsk salvage, System
# Volume Information = Windows shadow-copy dir, plus generic Windows / macOS
# index files).
DrK/FOUND.*/
DrK/System Volume Information/
DrK/$RECYCLE.BIN/
DrK/Thumbs.db
DrK/desktop.ini
DrK/.fseventsd/
DrK/.Spotlight-V100/
DrK/.Trashes/

# DrK/ — operator research notes for Dr. K's Tour content (kept local)
DrK/
